<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <style>

    .box{ width: 50px; height: 50px; }
    
    .ex-1 .parent-div{ background: #bbb; border: 2px solid black; width: 400px; } 
    
    .ex-1 .child-div-1{ background: yellow; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-2{ background: red; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-3{ background: blue; position: relative; top: 20px; left: 70px; }
    .ex-1 .child-div-4{ background: gray; }
        
    </style>
</head>
<body>

  <p>When the position is set to relative, the element will still hold the original place in the document flow.</p>
  <p>Then with top/right/bottom/left, the element can be moved to the relative place</p>
  
  <div class="ex-1">
    <h4>ex-1</h4>
    <div class="parent-div">
      <div class="child-div-1 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-2 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-3 box"></div>
      <div class="child-div-4 box"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
